main event: Radar detection of two unidentified flying objects near the Lisburne AFS radar site in Alaska
interesting points: The objects were tracked on radar for approximately 20 seconds before disappearing.
The objects were tracked on a westerly course at approximately 70-80 knots.
No visual observations of the objects were made.
The report includes numerical data, but no photographs.
The location of the sighting was Lisburne AFS, Alaska.
